   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>Subject One Hundred Seventy-seven TURNING FROM IDOLS TO GOD Scripture: 1 Thes 1:9 Man forsook God Man is created by God and belongs to God.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Due to his sin, man forsook God.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Man today is living a life of forsaking God.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>Man worshipped idols Sin causes man to forsake God.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>It also causes him to worship idols.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>The result of man s sin is the worship of idols.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Man worships idols because he has sinned and has lost God.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>God is the source of all peace and blessing.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>To lose God is to lose all peace and blessing.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Once man lost the source of peace and blessing, he turned to idols.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>The more man sins, the more he loses his peace, and the more he loses his peace, the more he wants it.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>This psychological craving for peace and blessing turns him to idols.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>No one who worships idols loves them.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>All the idol worshippers are just trying to utilize the idols.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>The life of man today is a life of idol worship.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>Some idols are tangible; others are intangible.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>Whatever takes the place of God in a man is an idol.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>Whatever a man relies on, apart from God, is also an idol.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The fallacy of idols Idols are false; hence, they are a deception.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>List facts to show that idols are false.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>The reality of God God is real and therefore trustworthy.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>Use examples to show how secure it is for man to trust in God.</S>
   <S PAR='23' RSNT='1' SNO='23'>Forsake idols and turn to God Since idols are a deception, we should forsake them.</S>
   <S PAR='24' RSNT='1' SNO='24'>Those who would not forsake them are fools.</S>
   <S PAR='25' RSNT='1' SNO='25'>They are either deceiving themselves, or are deceiving others.</S>
   <S PAR='26' RSNT='1' SNO='26'>Since God is trustworthy, we should turn to Him.</S>
   <S PAR='27' RSNT='1' SNO='27'>If we do not turn to Him, we are in a deception, either deceiving ourselves or deceiving others.</S>
   <S PAR='28' RSNT='1' SNO='28'>How to forsake idols to turn to God Recognize the fallacy of idols and the reality of God.</S>
   <S PAR='29' RSNT='1' SNO='29'>Destroy all of the idols in your home.</S>
   <S PAR='30' RSNT='1' SNO='30'>Repent and turn to God.</S>
   <S PAR='31' RSNT='1' SNO='31'>Receive the Son of God, Jesus Christ, as your Savior.</S>
   <S PAR='32' RSNT='1' SNO='32'>Worship and serve God through the Lord Jesus Christ.</S>
   </TEXT>
